<hl>
<seg id=1> China planned to fill in a million hectares of the ocean in the next century to settle down 30 million people. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> French News Agency, Beijing According to "China Daily" English version yesterday, China planned to fill in the ocean to settle down 20 to 30 million people along the coastal areas. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> At the Filling-Earth Meeting in Xiaoshan, Zhejiang Province, the government wanted to fill in a million hectares of the ocean along 18,000 km of coastal areas in the next 40 - 50 years. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to "China Daily", in the next century 20-30 million people would settle themselves down in these areas. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Professor Yu Zhiyin said:" Technically, there is no problem for China to fill in the ocean, but the problem is the shortage of money." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It's reported that although the plan would cause big problems in the environment, "it's still a magic weapon for improving the shortage of earth resources in the next century, especially because of the large population in China". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> And the plan could also provide new industries and more employment. </seg>
<seg id=8> China planned to invest in basic installations to remove the effect of the Asian financial crisis. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Vice Secretary-General of the meeting Zuo Zhongmo said: "It's not only a problem of agriculture, but the earth can provide comprehensive development in various areas including forestry, industry and tourism."  " </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Although China carries on a "one-child" policy, it's estimated that the population in China will continue growing. Until the middle of the next century, the population will reach 1600 million. </seg>
<seg id=11> Now the population in China is 1230 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Over 90% of the population is on one-third of the earth. </seg>
</p>
